    "body": "You are right. I wanted to make a simplified model and I have just run it without seeing the graphs. I wanted to plot a column, but anyway here are both cases (row and column) and they are slower than direct MPL.\n\n```\ndf = pd.DataFrame(data=np.random.normal(0, 1, (1,1000)))\ndfT = pd.DataFrame(data=np.random.normal(0, 1, (1000,1)))\n\n%timeit plt.plot(df.index, df.values)\n1 loops, best of 3: 2.15 s per loop\n%timeit df.plot()\n1 loops, best of 3: 11.1 s per loop\n\n%timeit plt.plot(dfT.index, dfT.values)\n100 loops, best of 3: 3.64 ms per loop\n%timeit dfT.plot()\n1 loops, best of 3: 236 ms per loop\n```\n"
