    "body": "You are still not comparing the right plots. Here is an apples-apples comparison in that they produce the same number of graphs with the same layout. Pandas does quite a bit of inference then simply calls `plt.plot()`.\n\n```\nIn [5]: %timeit dfT[0].plot()\n1 loops, best of 3: 9.46 ms per loop\n\nIn [10]: %timeit plt.plot(dfT[0].index,dfT[0].values)\n1000 loops, best of 3: 864 us per loop\n```\n"
